# Solar Domain Model

- `InstallationSite` is the root location entity and stores name and coordinates.
- Each `InstallationSite` has one or more `SolarPanel` entities.
- Each `SolarPanel` has exactly one `TiltMeasuringUnit`.
- Each `SolarPanel` has exactly one `CurrentMeasuringUnit`.
- Each `SolarPanel` has one or more `LinearMotor` entities.

# Hardware Model

- A `TiltMeasuringUnit` uses one GPIO pin for reading.
- A `CurrentMeasuringUnit` uses one GPIO pin for reading.
- A `LinearMotor` uses two GPIO pins for movement control: move up and move down.

# Domain Constraints

- Tilt values are represented as `readonly record struct TiltMeasurement(double Degrees, DateTime Timestamp)`.
- Valid tilt ranges are `0` to `90` degrees.
- Automatic motor movement is allowed only when the absolute delta between measured and target tilt is greater than `1` degree.

# PVGIS

- The target tilt is determined per installation site using latitude and longitude.
- PVGIS results must be cached to avoid unnecessary repeated remote calls.
